**Tests (acceptance = end-to-end with StubRunner):**
- Build a real run with capture (capture a stage into a temp repo via initCaptureRepo/execute + writeFile, exactly like run_test.go), recording the repo HEAD as git_sha so worktree.Checkout succeeds.
- Happy path: inject StubRunner{Concat:true} (or CannedOutput) via replayRunner.newRunner; run `replay <run> <stage>`; assert emitted Output to stdout (and to --output file in a second case) equals the expected concat/canned bytes. Assert worktree + scratch are cleaned up (no leftover temp dirs / `git worktree list` clean).
- Error cases: unknown run -> contains \"not found\"; unknown stage -> ErrStageNotFound message lists available names; missing/short git_sha -> ErrInvalidSHA/ErrSHANotFound surfaced; runner failure via StubRunner{Err: ...} -> error surfaced; no --runner & no config -> friendly \"no runner configured\" error.
- Run-id validation reuse: invalid run id rejected before git (assert wording matches run show).
- Registration smoke test: `replay --help` mentions replay/runner/output (replaces the removed reject case).
- Use injected StubRunner so tests never shell out; an ExecRunner integration path can use a tiny `cat`/`sh` echo script writing \\$ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE if a non-stub case is wanted, but the acceptance criterion is satisfied by StubRunner alone.

