**Risks:**
- root_test.go TestFutureCommandNamesAreRejected WILL fail unless updated — flagged above; must edit in the same change.
- Whitespace-only --runner splitting cannot handle quoted args / shell pipelines; documented limitation, acceptable for this bead.
- worktree.Checkout requires the recorded git_sha to exist as a commit in the current repo; replaying a run whose sha is not present locally yields ErrSHANotFound (expected, surfaced clearly).
- Tier 1 (user-facing CLI orchestration composing storage + worktree + exec). A built-binary manual test IS required in Verify: build the binary, capture a stage in a scratch repo, run `etude replay <run> <stage> --runner \"sh -c 'cat \\$ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR/* > \\$ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE'\"` (or a stub-equivalent script), and confirm emitted output + clean error messages for unknown run/stage and missing runner.

